originalText.text: I parked here last weekend for 2.5 hrs. ($25, booked through SpotHero).  Whoever parked my car struck something on the left rear corner of my car. I did not notice the damage when I picked my car up. I should have checked more thoroughly.  I noticed it when I got home. To fix it properly will cost over $500. I'm not happy. I can't recommend them. Clearly, they don't care if they damage their customers' cars.

originalText.text: I arrived appx 7:30 PM on Thursday December 8. Before handing over my keys, I asked how much it would cost with an expectation to pick up the car at 8:00 the following morning. The employee conferred with his colleague and told me that it would be $36. The discussion between the two colleagues was in Spanish and (because my knowledge of Spanish is limited) I thought that 7:00 AM was discussed so I asked for a clarification. I was told that if I picked up the car between 7:00 and 8:00 the cost would be $36. I returned at 7:30 the following morning and was told the cost was $65 - a full day charge - because I had not picked up the car by 7:00. I explained what I had been told and that I would not have left my car there had I known that is how much the cost would be. I received a reply that the people on duty the night before were not currently on duty so (in essence) "I know nothing". Since they had my car I had no choice but to pay the extortionate price they claimed. I asked who I could call to complain and the staff pointed out a phone number on the receipt and that someone should be there to receive the call. I called and there was no answer. Lesson learned and I will never patronize this garage again. I will also actively advocate that others do not either.

originalText.text:
I wanted to give this place an updated review.
I’ve been parking here ever since we came back to work in the city for a hybrid model. And I must say, they are doing their job, that is to park the cars and retrieve them when it’s time. Their job is straight to the point, clearly what they expect day in and day out. I think as customers, maybe we should also learn to throw some ice breakers their way. A little hi, or hello will come a long way. After all, they are the ones who has to stay in the basement to watch for coming customers. A friendly face coming from the surface would make such a difference. And who knows, later on maybe they would take extra care on that accelerator or brake system.
I have no complaints. I still choose to park here even if that means walking 20 blocks down (both ways) to come to work.
